issue.title: Implement ServiceCollectingObserver

milestone.title: v2.0.0-beta.1 Release
milestone.description: These are features that are useful or important but would result in an API break requiring a new major version to release.

issue.body:
Until #33 can finally be cleanly resolved the best way to deal with having a collection of services is to:

1. Observe the bootstrapping process
2. On container creation iterate over service definitions
3. Determine if the service definition implements the type that you're looking for
4. Retrieve that service from the container
5. Do something with it.

This is an admittedly clunky process. It could be made better if we implemented our own mechanism for completing much of this process such that the end user has to:

1. Provide the mechanism which type of services to collect
2. Iterate over a collection of services matching that type
